				<p>IDB Deutschland continues to build on its record of success over the last 40 years with another year of sales and organisational growth. An investment programme of €14 million was concluded in 2014 with the opening of expanded storage, packing and new product development facilities in Neukirchen-Vluyn.</p>
				<p>Kerrygold continues to be the number one butter brand in Germany, in terms of value and volume. Beyond this, its sales performance was in-line with expectations with strong sales performances by Kerrygold Extra. Kerrygold Extra is the clear number two in the spreadable market and is continuing to grow market share. Cheese also performed very strongly with a near 100% increase in volumes.</p>
				<p>NPD continues to be at the heart of the IDB Deutschland business. In 2014, IDB launched Kerrygold Extra 400g, a new unsalted sweet cream butter and Kildery cheese which won gold at the Global Cheese Awards.</p>
